<!-- Applications -->
<section class="section bg-cream">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="section-header centered">
            <span class="section-eyebrow">Applications</span>
            <h2>Every Landscape Type. One Proven Approach.</h2>
        </div>
        <div class="three-col-grid">
            <div class="info-card">
                <div class="info-card-icon">⛳</div>
                <h3>Golf Courses</h3>
                <p>Fairways under water restrictions can't just cut days — they need smarter irrigation. Subsurface drip maintains playability while slashing usage, giving superintendents real-time zone control from anywhere on the course.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="info-card">
                <div class="info-card-icon">🏟️</div>
                <h3>Sports Fields &amp; Stadiums</h3>
                <p>Wet sidelines and inconsistent turf quality come from overhead irrigation. Sub-surface drip delivers uniform moisture with no surface wetness — no injuries, no missed game days from waterlogged fields.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="info-card">
                <div class="info-card-icon">🏢</div>
                <h3>Commercial &amp; HOA Properties</h3>
                <p>Property managers face water bills, resident complaints about overspray, and high maintenance labor all at once. DripSmart reduces all three — with remote monitoring so you catch issues before residents ever notice.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="info-card">
                <div class="info-card-icon">🌳</div>
                <h3>Trees, Shrubs &amp; Slopes</h3>
                <p>Steep grades cause runoff before water soaks in. Drip runs slowly enough that slopes absorb every drop — and deep root watering builds drought tolerance so you're less dependent on irrigation over time.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="info-card">
                <div class="info-card-icon">🌺</div>
                <h3>Garden Beds &amp; Planters</h3>
                <p>Ornamental plantings suffer most from inconsistent watering — both under-watering and fungal damage from overhead spray. In-line drip solves both problems while reducing weeding from dry inter-row areas.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="info-card">
                <div class="info-card-icon">🏘️</div>
                <h3>Residential Estates</h3>
                <p>High-end properties with complex zones, mixed turf, and specimen planting need irrigation that performs as a unified system — not a collection of mismatched zones. We design it right and back it with local service.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

